Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, and elevated ALT, suggesting possible liver involvement. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, supporting renal dysfunction and possible diabetic ketoacidosis. Immediate clinical evaluation and management are recommended.
